Universal standard deviation 1993 - 2025  / This can be changed 

This simple model is designed to identify FED policy (Liquidity) regime, and does not replace Chicago Fed National Financial Conditions Index. 

Formula, in simple 
Liquidity score = Changes in Fed Policy rates + Changes in Fed balance sheet expansion + Changes in Fed balance long-term bond purchases 

As it uses universal sigma, this model is not appropriate to identify short-term policy effort by FED. 

There are many limitations to this model. This was actually a beta version to check if code works but somehow it does bare minimum in recognizing each fed policy regime and 
With 

Chicago Fed National Financial Conditions Index / Highly recommend
https://fred.stlouisfed.org/series/NFCI

Fed balance sheet / Nominal GDP model   / Use for short and long term liquidity 
https://github.com/Antonio3708/Macro-Variables/tree/main/Total%20reserves%20at%20Fed

Fed balance sheet asset composition (Go to treasury securities tab)
